The paper deals with the problem of line spectral estimation, which is a signal processing problem related to compressive sensing. The paper proposes a new method based on tensor decomposition to improve the estimation performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including compressive sensing. 

The paper also involves structured tensor analysis, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as tensors are often used to represent network data. 

The proposed method also involves machine learning techniques, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper deals with signal processing and estimation, which is related to cs.SP (Signal Processing).
